passage_text: Kean. Meaning of the name Kean. Listen and learn how to pronounce Kean so you can get the correct pronunciation for this boy name. Meaning of the name Kean. MEANING: From cian “”ancient, enduring.”” In legend Cian Mac Mael Muad was the son-in-law of Brian Boru (read the legend) who led the armies from the province of Munster to victory over the invading Vikings at the Battle of Clontarf in 1014, a battle in which both he and Brian were killed.

Irish Meaning: The name Keane is an Irish baby name. In Irish the meaning of the name Keane is: Ancient. English Meaning: The name Keane is an English baby name. In English the meaning of the name Keane is: Sharp. Celtic Meaning: The name Keane is a Celtic baby name. In Celtic the meaning of the name Keane is: Tall and handsome.

Kean is an unusual first name for males but a very prominent last name for both adults and children (#7533 out of 150436, Top 5%). (2000 U.S. Census). Cian and Kian (#494 last year) are the popular varying forms of Kean (unlisted) ranked in the Top 1000. Kean /kean/ [1 syll.] as a name for boys means ancient; fighter; sharp, keen wit or eye. Kean is an alternate form of Cian (Irish, Gaelic). Kean is also a form of Keane (Irish, Gaelic, Old English): actor Edmund Kean. Kreatif forms: Keanna, Keanne.

Finally, the surname may be a variant of Keane, of Old Gaelic origin, and the Anglicized form of the Gaelic O'Cathain, the male descendant of Cathan, a personal name from cath, battle; this sept were located in West Clare. Variants of the surname include Keene, Keenes, and Keens. This interesting surname may derive from a number of possible origins. Firstly, the name may be of Anglo-Saxon origin, as a nickname for a brave or proud person, from the Olde English pre 7th Century cene, Middle English kene, fierce, brave, proud.

Keane /kea-ne/ [1 syll.] as a boys' name is pronounced keen. It is of Irish, Gaelic and Old English origin, and the meaning of Keane is fighter; sharp, keen wit or eye. Actor Edmund Kean. Kreatif forms: Kaene, Kelne, Keonne. Keane has 1 feminine form: Keena. Keane is an uncommon first name for males but a very popular last name for all people (#3121 out of 150436, Top 2%).
